      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/40/810",
      "text": [
        " اَلْقِرْمِزِ فَإِنَّ أَصْحَابَنَا يَتَوَقَّوْنَ عَنِ اَلصَّلاَةِ فِيهِ فَكَتَبَ «لاَ بَأْسَ مُطْلَقٌ وَ اَلْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.810 - Ibrahim ibn Mahziyar wrote to Abu Muhammad Imam Hasan ibn Ali (as), asking about praying in garments dyed with crimson (qirmaz), saying, \"Our companions avoid praying in it.\"\nThe Imam wrote back: \"There is no problem with it at all, and all praise is due to Allah (swt).\""
        ]
      }
    },
